      <h1 class='title'>UK Trade and Investment: Spring Supplementary Estimate 2004&#x2013;05</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='lords-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HL Deb 22 February 2005 vol 669 c78WS</cite>
      
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_78ws' title='Col. 78WS &mdash; HL Deb 22 February 2005 vol 669 c78WS' name='column_78ws' href='#column_78ws' rel='bookmark'>78WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0669P0-05083'>
        <a name='S5LV0669P0_20050222_LWS_23'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-david-sainsbury' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S5LV0669P0_20050222_LWS_23' title='Link to this speech by Mr David Sainsbury' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-david-sainsbury" title="Mr David Sainsbury">The Parliamentary Under-Secretary of State, Department of Trade and Industry (Lord Sainsbury of Turville)</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para" id="S5LV0669P0-05083">My right honourable friend the Secretary of State for Trade and Industry (Ms Hewitt) has made the following Written Ministerial Statement.</p><p id="S5LV0669P0-05084">Subject to parliamentary approval of the necessary Supplementary Estimate, UK Trade and Investment's resource DEL will be increased by &#x00A3;2,000,000 from &#x00A3;99,087,000 to &#x00A3;101,087,000. Within the DEL change, the impact on resources and capital are set out in the following table:
          <table>
          <tr>
          <td><span class="italic">&#x00A3; 000</span></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
          <td></td>
          <td><span class="italic">Change</span></td>
          <td><span class="italic">Voted</span></td>
          <td><span class="italic">New DEL Non-voted</span></td>
          <td><span class="italic">Total</span></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
          <td>Resource</td>
          <td>2,000</td>
          <td>101,087</td>
          <td>0</td>
          <td>101,087</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
          <td>Capital</td>
          <td>0</td>
          <td>248</td>
          <td>0</td>
          <td>248</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
          <td>Depreciation<sup>*</sup></td>
          <td>0</td>
          <td>-187</td>
          <td>0</td>
          <td>-187</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
          <td>Total</td>
          <td>2,000</td>
          <td>101,148</td>
          <td>0</td>
          <td>101,148</td>
          </tr>
          </table>
          </p><p id="S5LV0669P0-05085"><sup>*</sup> Depreciation, which forms part of resource DEL, is excluded from the total DEL since capital DEL includes capital spending and to include depreciation of those assets would lead to double counting.</p><p id="S5LV0669P0-05086">The change in the resource element of the DEL arises from;
          (i) utilisation of &#x00A3;2,000,000 from the unused balance of the department's end-year flexibility entitlement to meet the increased requirement for resources particularly in the regions and on inward investment.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
